On August 16, 2017, Second Lady Karen Pence visited the INECO Foundation, a neurological clinic in Buenos Aires, Argentina. She attended a presentation on art therapy, observed a therapy session with a stroke patient, and had a roundtable discussion with art therapy practitioners in the area. Afterward, she had lunch with Deborah Cooney and took a walk in the city. Later, she went to the Argentina Stock Exchange to listen to the Vice President give a speech to the business community. Mrs. Pence then visited the Teatro Colon with the First Lady of Argentina, Juliana Macri. Finally, she joined the Vice President to meet U.S. embassy employees and their families. The next day, she would participate in activities in Santiago, Chile.